    "headline": "LME Trading Halt Hits Metals Markets From Aluminum to Zinc",
    "summary": "Trading data showed the halt came into effect at 2:44 p.m. local time, and an update on the LME’s website showed an issue had been reported with its electronic trading platform, while other systems were operating as normal.  Markets remained halted as of 4 p.m. local time, which usually marks the start of daily electronic trading windows used to set closing prices.  The LME intends to restore service after closing prices, a spokesperson said in a separate statement.",
